  "texts": [
    "If K has characteristic > 0, then we understand that e K = ∞, so that the lemma trivially holds true.",
    "If p K ̸ = p, then L/K is tamely ramified and hence it has ramification bounded by 1.",
    "Suppose that K has residue characteristic p. We may assume that L/K is totally ramified and cyclic of degree p m.",
    "Let O K denote the valuation ring of K. By local class field theory, we have the reciprocity map",
    "so that any cyclic quotient of Gal(L/K) of degree dividing p m has maximal ramification break ≤ u."
